    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Ezekiel",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 25,
        "summary": "The Lord's vengeance will fall on the Ammonites, on the Moabites and Edomites, and on the Philistines.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The word of the Lord came again unto me, saying,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Son of man, set thy face against the Ammonites, and prophesy against them;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 19:38 (36\u201338).",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And say unto the Ammonites, Hear the word of the Lord God; Thus saith the Lord God; Because thou saidst, Aha, against my sanctuary, when it was profaned; and against the land of Israel, when it was desolate; and against the house of Judah, when they went into captivity;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, therefore I will deliver thee to the men of the east for a possession, and they shall set their palaces in thee, and make their dwellings in thee: they shall eat thy fruit, and they shall drink thy milk.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will make Rabbah a stable for camels, and the Ammonites a couchingplace for flocks: and ye shall know that I am the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 49:2; Ezek. 21:20; Amos 1:14.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 117
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For thus saith the Lord God; Because thou hast clapped thine hands, and stamped with the feet, and rejoiced in heart with all thy despite against the land of Israel;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0contempt (malice).",
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 137
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, therefore I will stretch out mine hand upon thee, and will deliver thee for a spoil to the heathen; and I will cut thee off from the people, and I will cause thee to perish out of the countries: I will destroy thee; and thou shalt know that I am the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 251,
                        "end": 253
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thus saith the Lord God; Because that Moab and Seir do say, Behold, the house of Judah is like unto all the heathen;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 15:1.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 35:2 (1\u201315).",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heathen.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore, behold, I will open the side of Moab from the cities, from his cities which are on his frontiers, the glory of the country, Beth-jeshimoth, Baal-meon, and Kiriathaim,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Josh. 12:3.",
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 149
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Chr. 5:8.",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 160
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Unto the men of the east with the Ammonites, and will give them in possession, that the Ammonites may not be remembered among the nations.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will execute judgments upon Moab; and they shall know that I am the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thus saith the Lord God; Because that Edom hath dealt against the house of Judah by taking vengeance, and hath greatly offended, and revenged himself upon them;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 137:7.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore thus saith the Lord God; I will also stretch out mine hand upon Edom, and will cut off man and beast from it; and I will make it desolate from Teman; and they of Dedan shall fall by the sword.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 49:7.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mal. 1:3.",
                        "start": 139,
                        "end": 147
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will lay my vengeance upon Edom by the hand of my people Israel: and they shall do in Edom according to mine anger and according to my fury; and they shall know my vengeance, saith the Lord God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 34:5; Jer. 49:17 (7\u201322); Amos 9:12; Obad. 1:18 (8, 18\u201319, 21).",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thus saith the Lord God; Because the Philistines have dealt by revenge, and have taken vengeance with a despiteful heart, to destroy it for the old hatred;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 14:31 (29\u201332); Jer. 47:1; Amos 1:8.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 135
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore thus saith the Lord God; Behold, I will stretch out mine hand upon the Philistines, and I will cut off the Cherethims, and destroy the remnant of the sea coast.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zeph. 2:5 (4\u20135).",
                        "start": 160,
                        "end": 163
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will execute great vengeance upon them with furious rebukes; and they shall know that I am the Lord, when I shall lay my vengeance upon them.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}